modules.description: Handles file path manipulation, content reading, and writing with byte and string data. Operates on file paths, buffers, and raw byte sequences. Used to load configuration files, log data, and serialize binary structures.

Provides functions to submit code files to MOSS for similarity analysis, retrieve results, and parse XML responses. Works with file paths, byte arrays, and XML data structures. Used to detect code duplication in academic assignments and software projects.

Loads and manipulates file paths, reads and writes byte and string data, and handles serialization of binary structures. Processes configuration files, logs, and raw data through file system operations. Supports buffer management and content transformation for input and output. Can read binary logs, parse configuration files, and write serialized data to disk.
